Event: Death or Graft Failure

Fan Wu

2016-11-25

Data Manipulation

We use the ESRD patients listed for kidney transplantation in 2006 from 40 U.S. states. The time origin is set at the ESRD onset, which is the date of the first renal replacement therapy, either regulatory dialysis or kidney transplantation. The patients with pre-emptive transplantations are also included. We restriced to the patients who started their first renal replacement therapy after Jan. 1, 1995 The follow-up was until Dec. 4, 2015. The event of interest is patient death or graft failure. We exclude those patients

  • first start with dialysis but have no dialysis modality recorded (7%)
  • first start with dialysis but have unknown dialysis modality (3%)
  • first start with dialysis and change the modality of dialysis before TX (3%)
  • first start with dialysis but have no dialysis date recorded (15%)

We allow the renal replacement therapy of a patient change during the follow up, from dialysis to TX after receiving an allograft. Thus, the treatment is a time-dependent covariate. If the allograft fails, the date when he/she undergoes re-transplantation or reinitiate dialysis is used as the graft failure date.

We also adjusted for age at ESRD onset (18-40, 40-60, 60+), gender and race.

The number of patients, number of events, and censoring rates for each included states are as follows:
